The paper deals with the Traveling Salesman Problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and optimization. The paper focuses on the integrality gap of the subtour LP relaxation for circulant instances of the TSP. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.DM (discrete mathematics), cs.CC (computational complexity), cs.GT (discrete mathematics and combinatorial optimization), and cs.OC (optimization and control).
